  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add all the ingredients for the sauces into a bowl. Grate in the ginger and garlic and mix well."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice your chicken into long strips and place in a large mixing bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Whisk the two eggs and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make 2 bowls of flour mix, add 60g corn flour, 20g plain flour, ½ tsp baking soda to each mixing bowl. Season both bowls of flour with a pinch of salt and pepper and a tsp of garlic powder and onion salt."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now add the first bowl of flour mix to your chicken thigh strips and mix well. Pour the whisked eggs into the bowl of chicken. Then, one at a time, dredge a single chicken thigh strip into the second bowl of flour mix. Once they’ve all been coated, set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oil into a deep wok or pot until it reaches 180°C."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Fry the chicken in small batches (making sure to shake off any excess flour before placing in the oil) until they float to the top, this will take a few mins. Then place them on a paper-lined rack lined as this will help absorb any excess oil. You want the chicken to be super crispy so pop them back into the oil for a few mins again for the second round of deep-frying. Set aside your chicken in a deep bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "On medium heat, pour the sauce into a separate pot and cook for just a few mins until the sauce thickens a little."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour most of the sauce (set aside two tablespoons) onto the chicken and toss well."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Mix the remaining 2 tbsps of sauce with some mayo."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Garnish the chicken with toasted sesame seeds and sliced spring onions and enjoy with your sweet and spicy gochujang mayo."
    }
  ],
